LINQ

â€¢ LINQ is a Language Integrated Query

â€¢ LINQ provides the new way to manipulate the data, whether it is to or 
from the database or with an XML file or with a simple list of dynamic 
data.

 â€¢ LINQ is a uniform query system in C# to retrieve the data from 
different sources of data and formats such as XML, generics, 
collections, ADO.Net DataSet, Web Service, MS SQL Server, and other 
databases server.

 â€¢ LINQ provides the rich, standardized query syntax in a .NET 
programming language such as C# and VB.NET, which allows the 
developers to interact with any data sources


 --------Advantages of LINQ------
 â€¢ We do not need to learn new query language syntaxes for different sources 
of data because it provides the standard query syntax for the various data 
sources.
 â€¢ In LINQ, we have to write the Less code in comparison to the traditional 
approach. 
â€¢ LINQ provides the compile-time error checking as well as intelligence 
support in Visual Studio. This powerful feature helps us to avoid run-time 
errors.
 â€¢ LINQ provides a lot of built-in methods that we can be used to perform the 
different operations such as filtering, ordering, grouping, etc. which makes 
our work easy.
 â€¢ The query of LINQ can be reused

 -------Writing LINQ Query--------
 â€¢ LINQ queries return results as objects. It enables you to uses 
object-oriented approach on the result set and not to worry about 
transforming different formats of results into objects.
 â€¢ Each Query is a combination of three things; they are:
 1. Initialization(to work with a particular data source)
 2. Condition(where, filter, sorting condition)
 3. Selection (single selection, group selection or joining)
 â€¢ There are two basic ways to write a LINQ query to IEnumerable collection 
or IQueryable data sources.
 1. Using Query Syntax
 2. Using Method Syntax

LINQ------ Query-Syntax------
 Points to Remember (FOR QUERY SYNTAX)
 â€¢ As name suggest, Query Syntax is same like SQL (Structure Query 
Language) syntax.
 â€¢ Query Syntax starts with from clause and can be end 
with Select or GroupBy clause.
 â€¢ Use various other opertors like filtering, joining, grouping, sorting 
operators to construct the desired result.
 â€¢ Implicitly typed variable - var can be used to hold the result of the 
LINQ query

ğŸ”¸ 1. Syntax:
Query Syntax:
from emp in lstEmp select emp;

Method Syntax:
lstEmp.Where(emp => emp.Basic > 10000).Select(emp => emp.Name);
ğŸ”¸ Note: Always apply Where() before Select().

ğŸ”¸ 2. Anonymous Types:
Syntax:
